Date: 14 Apr 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Hong Kong - Department of Health [edited]
<http://www.info.gov.hk/dh/new/index.htm>

Situation report on atypical pneumonia 14 Apr 2003
The following is jointly issued by the Department of Health and the
Hospital Authority:
As of 3 PM 14 Apr 2003, an additional 40 patients with symptoms of atypical
pneumonia were admitted to public hospitals. They include 4 healthcare
workers (2 from Kwong Wah Hospital, one from Prince of Wales Hospital, and
one from Shatin Hospital) and 5 patients from Amoy Gardens. The remaining
31 were new patients and contacts of patients with atypical pneumonia.
A total of 229 patients have recovered from atypical pneumonia and have
been discharged from public hospitals. Of them, 6 were discharged
today. 124 patients are receiving treatment in intensive care units.
7 patients died in hospitals last night and this morning, bringing to 47
the total number of deaths relating to atypical pneumonia. 2 women with a
history of chronic disease, aged 74 and 67, died in Kwong Wah Hospital. 2
men, aged 49 and 78, died in Princess Margaret Hospital. A 69-year-old
female and a 74-year-old male with a history of chronic disease died in
Prince of Wales Hospital. Another 95-year-old female with a history of
chronic disease died in United Christian Hospital.
The cumulative figure for patients who have been admitted to public
hospitals with atypical pneumonia since 12 Mar 2003 is as follows:
Nature: Cumulative no. cases/ no. discharged/ no. deaths
Health care workers of Hospitals/Clinics and medical students: 280/ 93/ 47
Patients, family members & visitors: 910/ 136/ 0
Total: 1190/ 229/ 47
