[4]
Date: 14 Apr 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Taiwan Center for Disease Control [edited]
<http://203.65.72.83/En/dpc/ShowPublication.ASP?RecNo=856>

Taiwan SARS Updated on 13 April 2003
As of 9:00 AM on 13 April 2003, there were 153 possible SARS cases
reported. They include 23 probable, 37 suspected, 71 excluded, and 22
pending cases. In accordance with WHO guidelines, 7 of the 23 probable and
21 of the 37 suspected cases were discharged to home quarantine while the
other 16 probable and 16 suspected cases are still being cared for in
negative pressure rooms. A total of 70 possible SARS cases have been
discharged from hospitals.
As of 12 Apr 2003, local health stations distributed SARS home quarantine
notifications to 1545 persons who had close contact with probable SARS
cases. 1097 of them have been relieved of the quarantine order.
On 12 Apr 2003, a total number of 10 passengers arrived in the CKS
international airport had fever symptom and 3 of them sent to hospitals for
further medical services.
